        <prj:name>SS433</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We propose to use ALMA band 6 to obtain a full-polarisation image of the jets of the Galactic microquasar SS433 at 230 GHz and with a resolution of 0.19". Combining this observation with specifically commissioned radio data, and with unique high cadence optical spectra from our own dedicated data stream, the Global Jet Watch Network, we will answer questions concerning the energetics of the relativistic jets, modes by which the plasma bolides lose energy, the nature of the magnetic fields in the jets, and the interactions between the jets, accretion disk wind, and magnetic fields.</prj:note>
